howed Weissenberg tripping ahead of her 110m hurdle race in the women's heptathlon event and then rolling her ankle and falling to the floor.\", \"from\": 649, \"to\": 799, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Weissenberg was in tears as she was helped up by several medics and had her head in her hands as she was taken out of the arena by a wheelchair.\", \"from\": 801, \"to\": 945, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'I missed that, I was looking down but I missed that,' BBC commentator Steve Cram said.\", \"from\": 947, \"to\": 1034, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1002, \"end\": 1005, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\", \"score\": 0.9999972781796012, \"rank\": 2.7190200700827016e-06, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\"}, {\"begin\": 1018, \"end\": 1028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Cram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Steve Cram\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Cram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Cram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'She was hopping from hitting the hurdle, that could be an ankle.\", \"from\": 1036, \"to\": 1101, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She definitely turned her foot.'\", \"from\": 1102, \"to\": 1134, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'You can imagine how bitterly disappointed she will be,' another pundit said.\", \"from\": 1136, \"to\": 1213, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'You think you have done everything to prepare and something minor happens on your final preparations.'\", \"from\": 1215, \"to\": 1318, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Weissenberg, who is ranked ninth in the world, pulled out of the competition following the injury blow, with the German Athletics Association confirming she suffered a torn Achilles tendon in her left foot.\", \"from\"